Task: Implement strict functional logic and UI refinements for the Corefinity Control Panel Phase 1.
​1. Environments: The Sequential Deployment Flow (Image 11):
​In the Environments > Deployments tab, create a "New Deployment" card.
​Logic: Define 4 state-dependent dropdowns: Pipeline, Provider, Repository, and Branch.
​Behavior: Provider is disabled until Pipeline is selected. Repository is disabled until Provider is selected, and so on.
​Validation: If the Provider selection shows no linked accounts, display a red warning: "No account connected. Link your GitHub/Bitbucket in Profile > API Tokens."
​2. Tickets: The Communication Clarity (Image 34):
​In the Ticket View, implement the "Dual-Input" system.
​Staff Note (Internal): Label it "Internal Comment." When selected, the textarea border becomes Yellow, the background becomes #FFFBEB, and the button says "Post Staff Note."
​Customer Reply (External): Label it "Send Reply." When selected, the UI uses brand-orange accents and the button says "Reply to Customer."
​Ticket Context: Ensure the sidebar prominently displays the Agency, Company, and Website as OrangeLink components.
​3. Deployment Tasks: Real-time Simulation (Image 26):
​In the Environments > Deployment Tasks tab, create a list where the top item has a "Running" status with a pulsing Green dot.
​Add a "Rollback" button to previous successful tasks.
​4. Navigation & Breadcrumbs:
​Ensure the top header breadcrumb updates dynamically: All Clients > [Company Name] > [Website Name].
​All text referring to Companies, Websites, or Environments must be the specific Corefinity Orange and act as a functional link.
​5. Refined Tables:
​Use divide-y divide-gray-200 for tables. Add a subtle hover effect (hover:bg-gray-50) to rows in the Ticket Listing and Environment Pods screens to give it a premium feel.
